2 unit(s) Chicken Breasts
113 g Spring Mix
1 unit(s) Tomato
3 unit(s) Radish
¼ cup Feta Cheese, crumbled
28 g Croutons
3 tbsp Yogurt Sauce
1 tbsp Shawarma Spice Blend
1 tbsp White Wine Vinegar
0.13 tsp Salt*
½ tsp Sugar*
1.5 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat.
Meanwhile, pat chicken dry with paper towels, then dice into 1-inch pieces.
Season with salt, pepper and Shawarma Spice Blend.
When the pan is hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then chicken. Sear until golden-brown and cooked through, 3-4 min per side.**

Meanwhile, halve radishes lengthwise, then cut into thin half-moons.
Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.

Meanwhile, add vinegar, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) sugar and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil to a large bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then whisk to combine. (NOTE: This is your salad dressing.)
Add spring mix, tomatoes, radishes and croutons to the bowl with dressing. Toss to combine.

Divide salad between plates. Top with chicken.
Drizzle yogurt sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with feta cheese.

If you've opted to get chicken breasts, cut into 1-inch pieces, then cook them in the same way the recipe instructs you to cook the diced chicken.